As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 954 people, 386 households, and 270 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Gulf+Stream+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|access-date=June 25, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 786 people, 332 households, and 234 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Gulf+Stream+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|access-date=October 1, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 716 people, 340 households, and 222 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|953.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 625 housing units at an average density of {{convert|832.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 95.39% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (93.2% were [[Non-Hispanic White]]),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muninetguide.com/states/florida/municipality/Gulf_Stream.php |title=Demographics of Gulf Stream, FL |publisher=MuniNetGuide.com |access-date=December 3, 2007}}</ref> 0.98% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.14% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1.40% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1.12% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.98% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 2.93% of the population.

In 2000, there were 340 households, out of which 16.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.6% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 1.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 34.7% were non-families. 28.8% of all households were made up of individuals, and 18.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.11 and the average family size was 2.55.

In 2000, in the town, the population was spread out, with 14.9% under the age of 18, 1.7% from 18 to 24, 15.6% from 25 to 44, 29.7% from 45 to 64, and 38.0% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 56 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 89.1 males.

In 2000, the median income for a household in the town was $146,985, and the median income for a family was $186,777. Males had a median income of $78,045 versus $40,625 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $133,651. About 2.5% of families and 2.5% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], none under age 18 and just 1.7% of those age 65 or over.

As of 2000, [[English language|English]] spoken as a [[first language]] accounted for 97.54% of all residents, while the [[mother tongue]] of [[Spanish language|Spanish]] made up 2.45% of the population.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=place&zip=&place_id=28275&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA Data Center Results for Gulf Stream, Florida |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |access-date=December 3, 2007}}</ref>

